    <topic name="gas">
      <category>
        <pattern>*</pattern>
        <template>
          I can only tell you about saving gas
        </template>
      </category>
      <category>
        <pattern>tell me more</pattern>
        <template>
          According to moneyhelper.org.uk, the best way to save money on gas is simply to use less, pay by direct debit (as it is usually cheaper and you physically can't really miss a payment with it) and make your home more eco-friendly. Adding things such as better insulation, a new boiler, or solar panels could greatly reduce your gas bill.
        </template>
      </category>
    </topic>


    <topic name="electricity">
      <category>
        <pattern>*</pattern>
        <template>I can only tell you about saving electricity</template>
      </category>
      <category>
        <pattern>LED</pattern>
        <template>
          LED bulbs are more energy efficient than incandescent or fluorescent bulbs. On average, an incandescent light may last around 1000 hours. A fluorescent bulb producing the same amount of light may last around 8000 hours. However, an LED bulb may last around 25000 hours.
          While the price of an LED bulb is higher than other types of bulbs, the amount of energy they save over time makes it worthwhile. The price of running a 60-Watt incandescent bulb for 20 years (with 6 hours per day) is $360 USD. The price of running a 60-Watt LED bulb for the equivalent amount of time is $72.
        </template>
      </category>
      <category>
        <pattern>* light bulbs *</pattern>
        <template>
          <srai>LED</srai>
        </template>
      </category>
