      <category>
        <pattern>PLUG</pattern>
        <template>Electronics that are turned off and set to stand-by, but are still switched on at the plug still use electricity so that they can be switched back on</template>
      </category>
      <category>
        <pattern>* plug *</pattern>
        <template>
          <srai>PLUG</srai>
        </template>
      </category>
      <category>
        <pattern>SWITCHES</pattern>
        <template>
          Smart switches, like timed plugs or mobile-operated plugs can be used to turn off electronics without needing direct interaction from the user. An example of where this could be used is using a timer plug to switch off the house’s internet router when people are out of the house or asleep and thus not using the house’s internet.
          Smart switches also exist for light bulbs.
        </template>
      </category>
      <category>
