      </category>
      <category>
        <pattern>FRIDGEFREEZER</pattern>
        <template>Adjusting the temperature settings of the fridge and freezer to the optimum ranges can increase the life of the fridge as it will allow the fridge to run more efficiently. This also helps to reduce electricity costs. The optimum temperature for a fridge is between 3 to 5°C. The optimum temperature for a freezer is between -17 to -12°C.</template>
